    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect UL bandwidth TBS limit calculation in BWP configuration\n\n### Summary\nIn the `configure_UE_BWP` function, there was a bug where the DL bandwidth TBS limit was being overwritten with the UL bandwidth TBS limit calculation. This caused incorrect TBS limit values to be used for DL scheduling, potentially leading to incorrect MCS selection and reduced throughput.\n\nThe issue was in lines 2326-2327 of `gNB_scheduler_primitives.c` where both lines were setting `sc_info->dl_bw_tbslbrm`, with the second line incorrectly using the UL function.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Fixed line 2327 to correctly set `sc_info->ul_bw_tbslbrm` instead of overwriting `sc_info->dl_bw_tbslbrm`.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure a UE with different DL and UL initial BWP sizes\n2. Monitor the TBS limit values used in DL scheduling\n3. Observe that the DL TBS limit incorrectly reflects the UL BWP size instead of the DL BWP size\n4. This can result in suboptimal MCS selection and reduced DL throughput\n\nThe fix ensures that both DL and UL bandwidth TBS limits are correctly calculated and stored, which will improve the behavior of the initial DL BWP configuration.\n"
}